    "title": "Wan 2.1 image-to-video (masters)",
    "capability": "masters",
    "description": "Image + prompt -> animated webp master clip (Wan 2.1 I2V 14B, lightx2v lcm distill: 6 steps, cfg stays 1.0 - distilled, do not tune; shift 5). The plain image-to-video sibling of wan21_infinitetalk (no audio / no lipsync) — used by the WAN masters backend to seed CHARACTER shots from a crafted still so the cast stays on-model. Reuses the same --with-talking-head models + ComfyUI-WanVideoWrapper/VideoHelperSuite/KJNodes custom nodes (no extra downloads). Derived from the proven InfiniteTalk graph by dropping the audio path (LoadAudio/MultiTalkWav2VecEmbeds/Wav2VecModelLoader/MultiTalkModelLoader); node 309 is a real WanVideoDecode (VAE node 129 + sampler latents node 128), not the InfiniteTalk passthrough — validated live against WanVideoWrapper on an ep-021 b-roll still (2026-06-13, SSA-125). Output is SaveAnimatedWEBP so stage 3 rife / stage 4 assemble consume it exactly like a zeroscope master.",
